== Modifying MMStartup.bsh ==

Hint: if you always want the SPIM plugin to be called when starting Micro-Manager, add the following lines to ''Fiji.app/MMStartup.bsh'':

 setAccessibility(true);
 
 import org.micromanager.MMStudioMainFrame.PluginItem;
 for (PluginItem plugin : gui.plugins_)
         if (plugin.className.equals("SPIMAcquisition")) {
                 plugin.instantiate();
                 plugin.plugin.show();
         }
